            <div id="about">
                <h2>About this recipe</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><b>Source: </b> I don't know where this came from, it is on an old handwritten index card</li>
                    <li>A solid go-to in our house</li>
                    <li>We usually make it vegan, but any other type of milk works as well</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div id="planning">
                <h2>Planning</h2>
                <p><b>Prep Time:</b> 10 minutes</p>
                <p><b>Cook Time:</b> 30 minutes</p>
                <p><b>Servings:</b> 4 <p>
            </div> 

            <div id="preparation">
                <h2>Preparation</h2>
                <h3>Equipment</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>9"x13" casserole dish</li>
                    <li>Oven</li>
                </ul>
                <h3>Ingredients</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Oats, 4 cups</li>
                    <li>Coconut Sugar, 1/4 cup</li>
                    <li>Cinnamon, 1 tsp</li>
                    <li>Baking Powder, 1 tsp</li>
                    <li>Salt, 1/2 tsp</li>
                    <li>Soy milk, 2 1/3 cups</li>
                    <li>Syrup, 1/4 cup</li>
                    <li>Lemon juice, 1 Tbsp</li>
                    <li>Lemon zest, 2 tsp</li>
                    <li>Blueberries, 1 1/2 cups</li>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Also works well with raspberries</li>
                    </ul>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div id="cooking">
                <h2>Cooking</h2>
                <ol>
                    <li>Preheat oven to 375Â°</li>
                    <li>Mix all dry ingredients in the pan</li>
                    <li>Add all wet ingredients, mix</li>
                    <li>Bake 30 minutes</li>
                </ol>

            </div>

            <div id="notes">
                <h2>Notes & Tips</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Any type of milk works, plant based or cow milk</li>
                    <li>Any type of apple should work, but will change the taste accordingly</li>
                    <li>Can add 1-2 scoops of unflavored protein powder to make higher protein</li>

                </ul>

            </div>

            <div id="Nutrition">
                <h2>Nutritition per serving</h2>
